# The Treble runs fully offline by default — NO env vars are required.
# Everything below is optional.

# ── QVAC (on-device AI) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override the pundit's model source: a local GGUF path, an HTTPS URL, or a
# pear:// model link. Default: the SDK's LLAMA_3_2_1B_INST_Q4_0 constant
# (downloaded on first use by @qvac/sdk).
# Get models from: https://docs.qvac.tether.io (or any llama.cpp-compatible GGUF)
# TREBLE_QVAC_MODEL=/path/to/model.gguf

# ── Solana devnet settlement (real-chain engine) ─────────────────────────
# Used only with --engine solana (requires @tetherto/wdk-wallet-solana and a
# funded devnet account — see README "Real-chain settlement").
# Get an RPC endpoint from: https://solana.com/rpc (devnet is public)
# TREBLE_SOLANA_RPC=https://api.devnet.solana.com

# ── UX ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Disable ANSI colors in the CLI/demo output.
# NO_COLOR=1
